Truncate the value $v_i$ at the lower or upper boundary ($l_i$, $u_i$):

$$
\hat{v_i} = \begin{cases}
    l_i & \text{if $v_i < l_i$}, \\
    b_i & \text{if $v_i > b_i$}, \\
    v_i & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
$$

Mirror the value $v_i$ at the lower or upper boundary ($l_i$, $u_i$):

$$
\hat{v_i} = \begin{cases}
    2l_i - v_i & \text{if $v_i < l_i$}, \\
    2b_i - v_i & \text{if $v_i > b_i$}, \\
    v_i        & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
$$
